            <p>JACOB VOORSANGER&#44;<lb/>
                HOUSTON&#44; TEXAS.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                546 North Fifth Street<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>THE SABBATH VISITOR&#44;<lb/>
                Cincinnati&#44; Ohio.<lb/>
                JACOB VOORSANGER&#44; EDITOR.<lb/></p>
            <p>Houston&#44; Texas&#44; July 2 1886<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>The papers have doubtlessly informed you of my success<lb/> in San Francisco.  From a financial point of view&#44; I have every reason to be<lb/> gratified.  In this hour of my success I turn to you&#44; my earliest and still<lb/> my most valued friend in this country&#44; to assure you that under God&#39;s bles&#45;<lb/>sing I will do my work like a man.  I will not sleep on a bed of roses<lb/> in San Francisco; to the contrary I will have a more difficult task than<lb/> I at first imagined&#44; but I do not shirk any responsibility&#44; and I bel&#45;<lb/>ieve I am equal to the emergencies that will present themselves Let me assure<lb/> you&#44; once again&#44; that I have not developed into a full&#45;fledged destruction<lb/>ist as you seemed to fear some time ago.  To the contrary&#44; with my enlarged<lb/> influence and my increased opportunities for good and useful work&#44; it<lb/> will&#44; before long&#44; become manifest to you that I cling as strongly as ever&#44;<lb/> not indeed&#44; to the traditional ritualism of the Synagogue&#44; but to the pure<lb/> teachings of the Thora&#44; the prophets and the sages&#44; and will make it my<lb/> object to demonstrate that conservative teachings are acceptable to American<lb/> Israelites.  I depart from here on July 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#44; and it will gratify me to receive<lb/> before that time&#44; a line from you expressing that good will&#44; that&#44; believe<lb/> me&#44; has been one of the stimulants of my upward career.  With kindest<lb/> regards to you and yours in which my family joins me&#44;<lb/> Sincerely Yours<lb/> Jacob Voorsanger.<lb/></p>
            </body>
